import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="location", y="precipitation", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of precipitation across locations?")
    ax.set_xlabel("Location")
    ax.set_ylabel("Precipitation")
    ax.axhline(y=data['precipitation'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax, label='Max Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, ax=ax, label='Min Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].map({'sun': 'Sunny', 'rain': 'Rainy', 'snow': 'Snowy'})
    sns.countplot(x='location', hue='weather', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in each location?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Weather', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['precipitation', 'temp_max']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='precipitation', y='temp_max', data=data, hue='temp_max', palette='coolwarm')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Temperature')
    plt.title('How does precipitation affect temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
